## How to read this

- **Diamond nodes** are decisions — a runtime condition the system
  evaluates. Edge labels (`yes`/`no`/numeric thresholds) make the
  condition concrete.
- **Rectangle nodes (coloured)** are **terminal outcomes** — the system
  has settled into one of three classes:
  - 🟢 **Happy** — full success path; user sees nothing unusual.
  - 🟧 **Degraded** — partial success; user may see a delay, a
    fallback option, or a reduced feature set. Acceptable per the ADR.
  - 🟥 **Failed** — full failure; user sees an error and a recovery
    path. Acceptable only because the ADR considered it less bad than
    the alternative.
- The **path your incident took** is the most useful question this
  diagram answers — log entries should reference the terminal-outcome
  node ID.

